    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of picture captions with July 16 article on black American veterans who returned to area of Tuscany where they fought in World War II</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A front-page picture caption on July 16 about black American veterans who returned to an area of Tuscany where many of their comrades were killed in World War II referred incorrectly in some copies to the three veterans shown. While they were part of a unit that fought in the region, they did not take part in the battle in the village of Sommocolonia on Dec. 26, 1944.</p>
        <p>A caption with the continuation of the article misstated the given name of an Italian shown with one American. He is Nardino Nardini, not Antonio Nardini.</p>
      </block>
